List of Swimming World's Pacific Rim Swimmers of the Year

This award was introduced in 1995, the year after two Australian swimmers Kieren Perkins and Samantha Riley became the first two Pacific Rim swimmers to be named as World Swimmer of the Year. It has subsequently been dominated by Australian swimmers, who have won 20 of the 24 awards given.Ian Thorpe has won six awards (five consecutively) and Susie O'Neill has won four (three consecutively). No other country has had its swimmers win more than one award. Thorpe and Leisel Jones, were the youngest to have received this award, winning for the first time at the ages of 16 and 18 respectively. Grant Hackett and O'Neill were the oldest to receive the award, at 25 and 27 respectively.

